&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an AI Safety Researcher with an ML focus, to join our team working on the &lt;a href=&quot;https://arxiv.org/abs/2502.15657&quot;&gt;Scientist AI&lt;/a&gt; agenda. In this role, you will contribute to our plan using your expertise in AI safety and your knowledge and experience of machine learning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help clarify which AI safety research questions are central to the &lt;a href=&quot;https://arxiv.org/abs/2502.15657&quot;&gt;Scientist AI&lt;/a&gt; agenda.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze proposed solutions to these research questions and develop novel solution ideas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Propose, design, and implement novel ML algorithms and experiments aimed at solving or testing complex AI safety problems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scrutinize the &lt;a href=&quot;https://arxiv.org/abs/2502.15657&quot;&gt;Scientist AI&lt;/a&gt; agenda and its fit into a bigger strategic picture for mitigating AI risk, in order to guide and prioritize experiments to answer critical safety questions efficiently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required skills and qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PhD in a relevant field is preferred but not required if the candidate demonstrates exceptional abilities or equivalent experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research experience in technical AI safety, ideally with a focus on AGI safety.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience proposing, designing and running ML experiments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with ML frameworks such as PyTorch or Tensorflow.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excitement to contribute to and shape the &lt;a href=&quot;https://arxiv.org/abs/2502.15657&quot;&gt;Scientist AI&lt;/a&gt; agenda.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work in a collaborative environment and contribute to collective research goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to discuss complex findings with team members from diverse technical backgrounds.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred skills and qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in some of the following AI safety research areas: agent foundations, AI control, frontier AI safety, eliciting latent knowledge, externalised reasoning, ambitious alignment schemes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Machine learning research publications in top-tier venues (e.g., NeurIPS, ICML, ICLR, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience fine tuning and post training language models.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we offer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to contribute to a unique mission with a major impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive health benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A minimum of 20 days vacation per year upon start&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A minimum retirement savings employer contribution of 4%&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous flexible benefits designed to contribute to your well-being&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A team of passionate experts in their field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A collaborative and inclusive work environment with offices in the heart of Little Italy, in the trendy Mile-Ex district, close to public transportation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About LawZero&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;LawZero is a non-profit organization committed to advancing research and creating technical solutions that enable safe-by-design AI systems. Its scientific direction is based on new research and methods proposed by Professor Yoshua Bengio, the most cited AI researcher in the world. Based in Montreal, LawZero’s research aims to build non-agentic AI that learns primarily to understand the world rather than to act in it, giving truthful answers to questions based on transparent and externalized probabilistic reasoning. Such AI systems could be used to accelerate scientific discovery, to provide oversigh

&lt;p&gt;As a true anchor within the Talent and Culture team, the chosen candidate will bridge the gap between a new talent&#39;s arrival and their growth within the company. This is a dual role: providing essential support to scout our future team members, and ensuring their administrative and human journey is flawless, from day one to payday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Operations &amp;amp; Culture&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this area, the person in this role becomes the go-to anchor ensuring structure and peace of mind for our team members.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The art of onboarding: Orchestrate the arrival of new team members (preparing contracts, welcome kits, equipment logistics, and introducing the company culture).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;First point of contact: Thoughtfully answer daily questions from team members regarding internal policies, vacations, or benefits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Payroll support: Ensure rigorous data collection and information validation to guarantee the accuracy of each payroll cycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administrative lead: Draft official documents (employment confirmation letters, contract amendments) and keep culture tools and policies up to date.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document management: Oversee the digital organization and filing of employee records with exemplary structure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Talent &amp;amp; Culture team support: Support various projects and initiatives driven by the department.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Talent Acquisition Support&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this area, the Coordinator acts as an operational right hand to ensure every application is handled with professionalism and efficiency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Visibility: Post career opportunities across various platforms and social networks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pipeline management: For specific roles, perform initial resume screening to identify profiles that match our needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Logistical coordination: For specific roles, organize interviews between candidates and internal teams (e.g., managing complex calendars).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Background &amp;amp; verification: Conduct professional reference checks and follow up on verification files.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Candidate liaison: Act as a key resource to ensure rigorous follow-up with candidates starting at the job offer stage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills and qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience: 2 to 3 years of experience in a Talent and Culture coordination role or a similar function. A very good foundation in Talent/HR support is essential.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Discretion and professionalism: Act with exemplary ethics and a high sense of responsibility when handling sensitive files.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rigor: Demonstrate consistent attention to detail and strong organizational skills, particularly in producing official documents and payroll follow-ups.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Agility and collaboration: Show agility in dynamically managing priorities and act as a true partner to all team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bilingualism: Mastery of both French and English, written and spoken, in order to support our international operations and collaborations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we offer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The chance to contribute meaningfully to a globally critical initiative&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive health benefits (including mental health and wellness management account)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;20 days of vacation per year upon start&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employer contribution of 4% to your retirement savings, with no required employee match&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Additional compensation totaling 8% of your salary

&lt;p&gt;LawZero is a non-profit building safe-by-design AI systems. We’re building the Scientist AI, an advanced AI system designed from the ground up to be both highly capable and safe. As we develop both general‑purpose Scientist AI models and safety guardrails for frontier LLMs, we need rigorous, independent evaluation of every capability and safety claim we make. We are looking for a Director of Evaluations to build, lead, and grow LawZero’s Evaluations Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a foundational hire. You will define what world‑class evaluation looks like at LawZero, build the team and infrastructure to deliver it, and ensure that evaluations remain independent of the main research stream so that capability and safety claims can be trusted both internally and externally by the wider AI and AI safety community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define LawZero’s evaluations strategy and roadmap, prioritising what needs to be measured and when, in close coordination with both research and product teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build up the Evaluations Team during your first 3–6 months, scaling to roughly 8–10 people across research, engineering, dataset and benchmark design, and red‑teaming.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate the team independently of the main research and product streams in order to avoid conflicts of interest, including designing novel benchmarks that can be applied apples‑to‑apples to evaluate both the Scientist AI and frontier LLMs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the design and construction of new datasets, tasks, and virtual or interactive environments to measure performance of the Scientist AI across&amp;nbsp; capabilities, safety (including honesty and goal-directedness), explainability, causal mechanisms and detecting adversarial attacks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead evaluation of the Scientist AI when deployed as a guardrail around frontier models, including its ability to comply with harm specifications, detect and block harmful responses, explain its decisions, and resist adversarial attacks such as jailbreaks, prompt injection, and data poisoning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and lead our automated and manual red‑teaming programmes, both in‑house and in partnership with external providers, to stress test the Scientist AI as a general‑purpose model and as a guardrail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the construction of internal tooling and infrastructure needed to run evaluations at scale, automating and standardizing the pipeline wherever possible.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As needed and where possible, directly support research and product streams with their own internal requirements w.r.t. evaluations and benchmarking to unblock and speed up.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own LawZero’s public communication of evaluation results, including model and system cards, technical reports, peer‑reviewed publications and blog posts, to build trust with the wider AI safety community.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent LawZero externally on evaluations and AI safety measurement, including engagements with AI safety institutes, research collaborators, and grant funders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills and qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An advanced degree (MSc or higher) in machine learning, computer science, or a closely related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of experience in machine learning, with at least 5 years in a leadership role building or scaling technical teams working on real-world ML products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands‑on expertise in designing and running large‑scale evaluations of LLMs or other frontier ML systems across capabilities, safety, and adversarial robustness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A track record of building evaluation datasets, benchmarks, or interactive environments from scratch, including for safety‑relevant properties such as hon

