&lt;p&gt;LawZero is seeking a curious, intellectually agile, and mission-driven &lt;strong&gt;Senior Researcher Communication Specialist - AI&lt;/strong&gt; to serve as a bridge between our research teams and external audiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working closely with researchers, engineers, and leadership, you will transform complex AI research into clear, engaging, and scientifically accurate content for a variety of stakeholders, including policymakers, funding organizations, partners, media, and the broader public.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires someone comfortable engaging directly with scientists, understanding advanced machine learning concepts, and translating technical breakthroughs into compelling narratives without losing scientific rigor.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Beyond content creation, you will play an important role in supporting research funding initiatives, helping researchers communicate technical requirements and scientific impact in grant applications and strategic communications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an ideal opportunity for someone who enjoys operating at the intersection of science, communication, and societal impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scientific Communication &amp;amp; Knowledge Translation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with researchers and engineers to understand ongoing projects, technical breakthroughs, and research outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate complex AI and machine learning concepts into accessible, engaging content tailored to diverse audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce a wide range of communication materials, including:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Blog posts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research summaries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;White papers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Newsletters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Website content&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Social media content&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Executive briefings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Government and stakeholder communications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure scientific accuracy while adapting content to varying levels of technical expertise.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Content Development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify emerging trends, research milestones, and opportunities to showcase LawZero’s work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate content ideas and recommend communication strategies that support organizational goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Repurpose research outputs into multiple content formats and channels to maximize visibility and impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Connect LawZero’s research activities with broader developments in AI, AI safety, and public policy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Grant Writing &amp;amp; Research Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the preparation of grant proposals and research funding applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft and refine technical sections related to:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AI research programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Computing infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;GPU requirements and resource planning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research methodologies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expected scientific outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work alongside researchers to streamline proposal development and reduce administrative burden.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scientific Outreach &amp;amp; Events&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in preparing conference materials, presentations, posters, and supporting documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to communications supporting partnerships, public engagement initiatives, and scientific outreach activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help position LawZero as a leading voice in responsible AI research.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;E

&lt;p&gt;In charge of technology, the IT department oversees CyberSecurity, End User support, and the management of the compute environment used to achieve our mission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a System Administrator, part of an agile team reporting to the IT Director, focused on the administration of our on-premise and cloud computing environments, supporting our mission to build safe-by-design AI systems.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be instrumental to our success by ensuring the availability, security, and performance of a platform containing hundreds of GPUs. You will have the opportunity to influence technical decisions and to work on a large variety of systems and hardware types in a cutting-edge environment. Your day-to-day will be spent between project-type work and operational management, with a security-focused mindset.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take part in the operations and day-to-day management of LawZero’s various platforms and environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support internal users with their compute requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement automation, using Infrastructure-as-Code (IaC) tools such as Ansible, Terraform, and shell scripts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure systems, network, and storage equipment are kept up-to-date and secure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Investigate hardware and software issues, and work with vendors for support and RMA requests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond to monitoring alerts and support requests in a timely manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Propose and implement improvements to the platform and our processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and evolve monitoring and alerting systems for performance and reliability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and enforce security hardening measures, ensuring compliance and implementing best practices across all compute infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document architecture and write standard operating procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills and qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;University degree in a relevant discipline or equivalent experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience in systems administration, or demonstrated mastery of complex, large-scale Linux environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep knowledge of Linux operation, configuration, and optimization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong network skills, including firewalls, routing protocols, switching, and technologies, such as Infiniband and Ethernet&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing storage arrays, and network and distributed file systems, such as Lustre and NFS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with distributed systems, such as Slurm or Kubernetes, an asset&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience administering High-Performance Computing (HPC) clusters, an asset&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customer-service mindset, able to understand and communicate with a variety of stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capacity to communicate technical concepts to a non-technical audience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in written and spoken English, mandatory. French, a strong asset&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent priority management skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we offer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to contribute to a unique mission with a major impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive health benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A minimum of 20 days vacation per year upon start&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A minimum retirement savings employer contribution of 4%&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous flexible benefits designed to contribute to your well-being&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A team of passionate experts in their field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A collaborative and inclusive work environment with offices in the heart of Little Italy, in the trendy Mile-Ex district, close to public transportation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;*This opening is planned for a July or August 2026 start date*&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Technical Recruiter to support the growth of our rapidly expanding organization, with a focus on teams working in the fields of artificial intelligence, machine learning, and AI Safety.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage several 360-degree recruitment mandates simultaneously, from defining the need to signing the offer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and execute targeted and creative sourcing strategies to identify and engage niche talent (Research Developers, Machine Learning Researchers, AI Safety Experts, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Approach, activate, and support passive candidates throughout the recruitment process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop comprehensive research plans: profile targeting, market mapping (local and international), competitive analysis, and creation of specialized talent pools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to market monitoring and talent positioning in the AI and technological markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with hiring managers, researchers, and technical leadership to clarify needs, prioritize roles, and define target profiles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the complete offer process: preparation, negotiation, presentation, and closing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Offer a consistent, smooth candidate experience tailored to the level of expertise of the profiles encountered.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in continuous improvement initiatives with internal teams (HR, compensation, engagement, accessibility) to optimize recruitment practices and tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills and qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A minimum of 7 years experience recruiting technical profiles, combined with a strong understanding of the language and challenges specific to AI research.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in a relevant field.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable evolving in a fast-paced (startup), rapidly transforming environment with grey areas and shifting priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and oral communication, in both French and English, to support our international operations and collaborations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we offer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The chance to contribute meaningfully to a globally critical initiative&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive health benefits (including mental health and wellness management account)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;20 days of vacation per year upon start&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employer contribution of 4% to your retirement savings, with no required employee match&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Additional compensation totaling 8% of your salary to apply towards additional retirement savings or bonuses (independent of group and individual performance)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A team of passionate world-class experts in their field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A collaborative and inclusive work environment in our vibrant office space in the heart of Little Italy, in the trendy Mile-Ex district, close to public transportation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About LawZero&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
